         <abstract>
            <p>An anonymous homily for the joint celebration of the feast of <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo">Saint George</persName> and <persName ref="PRS6819Mary">Saint Mary</persName>, 
               to be read on the 16th of Naḥāse. On this day, in the Ethiopian Orthodox Church, falls the feast of the Assumption of Saint Mary into heaven and the translation of the body (relics) of 
               Saint George from ‘Persia’ to his church in <placeName ref="LOC4355Lydda">Lydda</placeName>. 
               In the homily, the coincidence of these two feasts is explained not as a mere accident but as divine disposition.</p>
         </abstract>
